White illustrates the degree to which a common project emerged during those three decades. The book is bound together by White’s belief that these experiments are following in the idealism of Soviet silent filmmaker Dziga Vertov, who wrote about his notion of “the Radio Eye.” White also puts these experiments in the context of work by the Cuban filmmaker and theorist Julio García Espinosa and his notion of “imperfect cinema,” Jürgen Habermas and his notions of the “public sphere,” and Édourard Glissant’s ideas about “créolité” as the defining aspect of modern culture. This is a genuinely internationalist moment, and these experiments are in conversation with a wide array of thought across a number of languages.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCinémaxHistoirexFéroé. 0aCinémaxHistoirexIrlandexGaeltacht. 0aCinémaxHistoirexQuébec (Province). 0aCinémaxHistoirexTerre-Neuve-et-Labrador. 0aMotion picturesxHistoryxFaroe Islands. 0aMotion picturesxHistoryxIrelandxGaeltacht. 0aMotion picturesxHistoryxNewfoundland and Labrador. 0aMotion picturesxHistoryxQuébec (Province). 0aMotion pictureszFaroe IslandsxHistory. 0aMotion pictureszIrelandzGaeltachtxHistory. 0aMotion pictureszNewfoundland and LabradorxHistory. 0aMotion pictureszQuébec (Province)xHistory. 0aMotion pictureszQuébec (Province)xHistory. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978155458212940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781554582129423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781554582129/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 